 Another thing I've read about the &quot;seed&quot; idea comes from tradeskillers. Some of them claim after a couple failures in a row you should /random until you get high numbers 2-3 times in a row before doing more combines. Others say camp/zone. Both theories are meant to of course reset the RNG portion of the combine success/failure rate more in their favor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daedrea>Daedrea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/03 2:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: strings of hits</span><hr size=1> Haven't taken statistics much have ya?<br>
<br>
While its not a statistically high probability that things like multiple max hits / flurries happen, there is always the probability, every time you get hit.  With the amount of times you get hit as a main tank, the probability that this *doesn't* ever happen isn't especially high, though still high.  Evasive / LR / CS changes the &quot;weight&quot; of certain things happening, but only Defensive can stop you from getting flurried for 20k. :-P<br>
<br>
That said, having to base a CH chain on worst case scenarios really isn't the case anymore, and Evasive has certainly emerged as a very nice discipline.  Looking at that Xegony chart, the trend for her is overwhlemingly towards the bottom of the spectrum.  A lot of PoP mobs were made like this, to give them that godlike aura.  Don't let max hits fool ya. :-P <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=340675">Lich Daedrea Darksoul</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->65 Arch Lich<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.orderofdraconis.com">Order of Draconis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daedrea>Daedrea</A> at: 4/3/03 2:23:06 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showMessageRange?topicID=1881.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=1881.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=1881.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?topicID=1881.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.threadControl?topicID=1881.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.subscribeUnregiste